{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "8th of March \u201cInternational Women\u2019s Day\u201d to become a bank holiday",
        "additional_details": "Women\u2019s day should be recognised in the UK. It gives women the feeling of being recognised as mothers, grandmothers,  partners, sisters, daughters etc. It shows appreciation for everything women do, whether that\u2019s being a housewife or in business. This gives woman a sense of equality and empowerment. A great opportunity to use this day for different campaigns  against domestic abuse  and mental health issue where women still suffer.",
        "background": "International Women\u2019s Day celebrated in many countries and in some of them 8th of March  is an annual holiday for celebration. I would like for women in the UK to also have this opportunity and recognition. The 8th of March should become a bank holiday.",
